{"id": 8417, "date": "2019-03-27T05:00:00", "date_gmt": "2019-03-27T12:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=8417"}, "modified": "2019-12-04T19:18:46", "modified_gmt": "2019-12-05T03:18:46", "slug": "matr-the-dictators-and-bruce-springsteen-faster-and-louder", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2019/03/27/matr-the-dictators-and-bruce-springsteen-faster-and-louder/", "title": {"rendered": "MatR: The Dictators and Bruce Springsteen, Faster and Louder"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>I admit it: I&#8217;m reaching with this one.</p>\n<p>Technically, &#8220;Faster and Louder&#8221; qualifies for a <em>Meeting Across the River </em>blog entry, since Bruce does indeed make an appearance with The Dictators on the lead-off track to their 1978 album\u00a0<em>Bloodbrothers</em>.</p>\n<p>Bruce was a big fan of the influential punk band&#8217;s first two albums&#8211;in fact, he once wore a Dictators tee shirt on stage and dedicated &#8220;Born to Run&#8221; to them.</p>\n<p><img data-attachment-id=\"8419\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2019/03/27/matr-the-dictators-and-bruce-springsteen-faster-and-louder/dictators-bruce/#main\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/dictators-bruce.jpg?fit=400%2C553&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"400,553\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"dictators bruce\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/dictators-bruce.jpg?fit=217%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/dictators-bruce.jpg?fit=400%2C553&amp;ssl=1\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\" wp-image-8419 aligncenter\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/dictators-bruce-217x300.jpg?resize=758%2C1048\" alt=\"\" width=\"758\" height=\"1048\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/dictators-bruce.jpg?resize=217%2C300&amp;ssl=1 217w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/dictators-bruce.jpg?w=400&amp;ssl=1 400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /></p>\n<p>So when it turned out the band was recording their third album in the same building where Bruce was mixing <em>Darkness on the Edge of Town</em>, Bruce stopped by for a visit and ended up on vinyl.</p>\n<p>Blink and you&#8217;ll miss it, but at about the 2:10 mark, listen closely and you&#8217;ll hear Bruce count the band back in for the final chorus.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe class='youtube-player' width='758' height='427' src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/kMTAatF6FOI?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent' allowfullscreen='true' style='border:0;' sandbox='allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation'></iframe></span></div>\n<p>So yeah, it&#8217;s fleeting, but it&#8217;s a cool moment in the only collaboration between Bruce Springsteen and The Dictators.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Blink and you&#8217;ll miss it: &#8220;Faster and Louder&#8221; features the only collaboration between Bruce Springsteen and the legendary punk band, The Dictators.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 8418, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false